## Problem
When conversation resolution fails (network error), the code silently continues with `activeConversationId = null`:

```kotlin
// ChatViewModel.kt lines 385-408
private fun resolveConversationAndLoad() {
    viewModelScope.launch {
        if (activeConversationId == null) {
            try {
                conversationRepository.refreshConversationsIfStale(agentId, CONVERSATION_CACHE_TTL_MS)
                val conversations = conversationRepository.getCachedConversations(agentId)
                val mostRecent = conversations.sortedByDescending { ... }.firstOrNull()
                if (mostRecent != null) {
                    activeConversationId = mostRecent.id
                }
            } catch (e: Exception) {
                Log.w("ChatViewModel", "Failed to resolve conversation", e)
                // SILENTLY CONTINUES WITH NULL!
            }
        }
        loadMessagesInternal()  // Called even when conversationId is null
    }
}
```

This causes messages to be read from the wrong cache and creates inconsistent state.

## Solution
Make conversation resolution a required step. If it fails, show an error to the user with retry option instead of silently proceeding.

## Implementation

### Step 1: Create ConversationState sealed class
**File: `app/src/main/java/com/letta/mobile/ui/screens/chat/ChatViewModel.kt`**

Add before ChatUiState:
